<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[m]</span>en living along with them, or going to their Wigwams, <span class="AddHand-editors">[for]</span> let them have ever so little to Eat, it is Shar'd among them all, should it be Only a mouth full each, and when there is Several Wigwams and families at the same place, whoever Kills a Moose, or Deer or any other animal, Shares it among the whole, and has Some times the worse Share himself, and when the animal is too Small to be worth <span class="AddHand-editors">[sh]</span>areing among so many of them, it is Immediately Cooked, and made a feast of, to which Every One is invited, <span class="AddHand-editors">[let]</span> each share be Ever so little, they likewise make feasts <span class="AddHand-editors">[from]</span> which Boys, Women, and Children are Excluded, <span class="AddHand-editors">[thi]</span>s they Call Medicine, or Conjuring feasts, at whi<span class="AddHand-editors">[ch]</span> they observe a great many ridiculous Ceremo<span class="AddHand-editors">[ni]</span>es, such as Eating without a Knife, Striveing who <span class="AddHand-editors">[can]</span> <span class="AddHand-editors">[f]</span>inish his Share first, Dancing, walking so ma<span class="AddHand-editors">[ny]</span> <span class="AddHand-editors">[tim]</span>es round the fire, retireing One by One in rota<span class="AddHand-editors">[tion]</span> <span class="AddHand-editors">[and]</span> Several Other foolish Ceremonies, too tedious to <span class="AddHand-editors">[insert here.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[I]</span> <span class="AddHand-editors">[h]</span>ave Often been Invited to these grand feasts,</p>

